results.occurrenceRemarks: There were tons of swifts over the skies of Dubrovnik, of two species, Alpine and Common. The Alpine were most interesting to me because I'd seen the commons before in Sweden. I did manage to get a photo after much trying, but it's a bit blurry. Thought I'd post anyway because I though they were pretty cool looking birds with their white throats that bellies.
